					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Seems like a hardware solution would be to make the USB drive's cache memory internal to the USB drive, and it would have to be non-volatile RAM (like FRAM or something).  So if the device loses power before dumping the cache, it can finish that up next time it gets powered.   But I guess that would make it more expensive, and still not really solve the problem of a user being able to yank it out at any time.</div>

